    {
      "id": "1a9dcd25_219f6a05",
      "file_path": "ONAP-PDP-REST/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/pdp/rest/api/services/PDPServices.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 411,
      "message": "Sonar will complain about nested try/catch statements.\n\nOpening multiple resources in the try-with resources as shown on one of the answers at the stack overflow answer below looks tricky to implement in this case:\nhttps://stackoverflow.com/questions/884007/correct-way-to-close-nested-streams-and-writers-in-java\n\nThe JSON reader supports auto close but it is only used in one of the clauses in the if statement.\n\nMaybe Mike could have a look at this statement or maybe we should leave it?",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 2787,
        "name": "Liam Fallon",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "liam.fallon@est.tech",
        "username": "liamfallon"
      },
      "updated": "2018-07-13 12:24:19.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "1a9dcd25_6131f20a",
      "file_path": "ONAP-PAP-REST/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/pap/xacml/rest/components/PolicyDBDao.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 1937,
      "message": "The auto close used by try-with-resources is actually a better solution than the utility method.  As far I can tell the utility method was only used to ignore nulls here.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 805,
        "name": "Michael Mokry",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "michael.mokry@att.com",
        "username": "mmokry"
      },
      "updated": "2018-07-13 14:12:16.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "1a9dcd25_c1f8064c",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "1a9dcd25_842bec81",
      "file_path": "ONAP-PDP-REST/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/pdp/rest/api/services/PDPServices.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 411,
      "message": "Yeah this one is a bit tricky... I would like to look at this a little more and test a couple ideas locally.  I think we can keep this change though, it does eliminate one Sonar issue for try-with-resources, and since the nested trys were already existing it should not add any tech debt right.  Ideally I would like to attempt to get all this under one try block (if possible) but need to do some research to be sure.  Most likely we will have to break this down to smaller methods to avoid the complexity anyway, that may be the better solution.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 805,
        "name": "Michael Mokry",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "michael.mokry@att.com",
        "username": "mmokry"
      },
      "updated": "2018-07-13 14:12:16.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "1a9dcd25_219f6a05",
      "unresolved": false
    },
